{"parentUuid":"11d7479c-44e1-4e84-a17d-612b19f861d5","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a81b8b0ba69959f89","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq1VdY7xiWVEAwhxn4Xz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01N1FVw8kAHryNBUXETTy5He","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\acceptance.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":25507,"cache_read_input_tokens":19208,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":25507,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq1VcbZXaBsGoBi32H39","attributionAgent":"plan-audit","type":"assistant","uuid":"d5cb94a9-28da-4721-b049-0533922504a6","timestamp":"2026-07-08T17:47:06.472Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"d5cb94a9-28da-4721-b049-0533922504a6","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"baf21a5c-1a23-429e-9e74-122628363a90","agentId":"a81b8b0ba69959f89","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01N1FVw8kAHryNBUXETTy5He","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tcriteria_total: 22\n3\tdelegated_criteria: [AC22]\n4\t---\n5\t\n6\t# Acceptance criteria — per-customer metric quotas\n7\t\n8\tDefinition-of-done for this feature. Implementation builds to these; testing maps each ID to a test\n9\t(`criteria_covered`); the deploy gate requires `criteria_covered.total == criteria_total` and that\n10\tevery delegated id appears in `delegated_criteria` (only `security` is a valid delegate). Derived\n11\tfrom `.pipeline/requirements.md` (authoritative) + `PROJECT.md`.\n12\t\n13\t| ID | Criterion | File / layer | How verified |\n14\t|---|---|---|---|\n15\t| AC1 | `PUT /v1/quotas` (admin key + valid body) creates a quota → **201**, response echoes `{customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}`, exactly one `quotas` row persisted | `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_put_creates_quota_returns_201_and_echoes` |\n16\t| AC2 | `PUT /v1/quotas` replacing an existing `(customer_id, metric)` → **200**, `limit_per_window` updated, still exactly one row (upsert, no duplicate) | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` (`xmax` insert/replace) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_put_replace_returns_200_single_row` |\n17\t| AC3 | `PUT /v1/quotas` with an **ingest**-scoped key → **403**, envelope `code: forbidden`; admin scope required | `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/auth/api_key.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_ingest_key_forbidden` |\n18\t| AC4 | `PUT /v1/quotas` with missing/malformed/revoked auth → **401** | `src/auth/api_key.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_put_requires_auth` |\n19\t| AC5 | Validation: `limit_per_window` = 0/negative/non-integer → **422** `validation_failed`; unknown field → 422 (`extra='forbid'`); `customer_id`/`metric` outside allowlist → 422 | `src/api/schemas/quotas.py` | `tests/test_schemas_quotas.py` + `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_validation_rejections` |\n20\t| AC6 | Tenant isolation: a quota is stored under and enforced against the authenticated `api_key_id` only; a second tenant's key never reads/affects tenant A's quota (api_key_id scoping + RLS) | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `alembic/versions/0003_*`, `src/db/session.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_quota_is_tenant_isolated` |\n21\t| AC7 | `POST /v1/events` for a `(customer, metric)` with **no quota** → unchanged behavior (201, unlimited); no regression | `src/services/events_service.py` | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_no_quota_is_unlimited` |\n22\t| AC8 | `POST /v1/events` where `R + Q <= L` → **201** accepted, rollup increments normally | `src/services/events_service.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_under_limit_accepted` |\n23\t| AC9 | `POST /v1/events` where `R + Q > L` → **429** envelope `code: quota_exceeded` + `Retry-After` header (seconds to next hour); **no event row persisted and rollup not incremented** (transaction rolled back) | `src/services/events_service.py`, `src/api/errors.py` | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_over_limit_429_and_no_partial_write` |\n24\t| AC10 | `Q > L` against an **empty window** → **429** `quota_exceeded`; no rollup row created | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `src/services/events_service.py` | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_empty_window_q_gt_l_rejected` |\n25\t| AC11 | Idempotent replay of a previously-**accepted** event, window now over quota → **200** replay of the original stored result; quota **not** consulted; no usage added | `src/services/events_service.py` | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_replay_over_quota_returns_200_no_usage` |\n26\t| AC12 | A quota set/lowered **mid-window** takes effect immediately against the already-accumulated rollup (lowering `L <= R` blocks the rest of the window) | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` (fresh read per POST) | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_midwindow_change_takes_effect` |\n27\t| AC13 | Strict enforcement under concurrency: N concurrent **distinct-idempotency-key** posts of `Q` against `L` never drive `usage_rollup.total_quantity` above `L`; the excess are rejected 429 | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` (`FOR UPDATE OF q`), `src/services/events_service.py` | `tests/integration/test_quota_concurrency.py::test_concurrent_posts_never_exceed_limit` |\n28\t| AC14 | Throttle precedence: the Tier-2 per-key throttle (`code: rate_limited`) still fires before any quota logic; quota rejection uses the **distinct** `code: quota_exceeded` | `src/api/routes/events.py`, `src/api/errors.py` | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_throttle_precedes_quota_distinct_codes` |\n29\t| AC15 | `PUT /v1/quotas` is rate-limited by the **Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`** token bucket (principal-keyed, post-auth); two principals sharing one IP get independent buckets | `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/auth/rate_limit.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_put_rate_limited_per_principal` (two-principals-one-IP shape) |\n30\t| AC16 | Migration `0003` `up→down→up` restores schema + re-enforces all constraints (`quotas` PK/FK/`CHECK(limit>=1)`, `api_keys.scope CHECK IN ('ingest','admin')`); `quotas` is a create-migration (no row-survival across down); pre-existing `api_keys` rows survive the scope column add/drop (scope resets to `'ingest'` default — defined expand/contract behavior) | `alembic/versions/0003_*` | `tests/integration/test_quota_migration.py::test_0003_roundtrip_schema_and_constraints` |\n31\t| AC17 | `seed_api_key.py --admin` provisions a key with `scope='admin'`; without the flag `scope` defaults to `'ingest'` | `scripts/seed_api_key.py`, `src/repositories/api_keys_repo.py` | `tests/integration/test_seed_api_key_script.py::test_admin_flag_sets_scope` |\n32\t| AC18 | All new `quotas` SQL is parameterized (`text()` bind params only); an injection payload in `customer_id`/`metric` is rejected at the schema boundary (422) and never reaches the SQL sink | `src/api/schemas/quotas.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_injection_rejected_at_boundary` + security 6c (Semgrep) |\n33\t| AC19 | Observability/audit: a quota rejection logs `quota.rejected` (WARNING; `userId`, `action=deny`, `customer_id`, `metric`, `reason` — **no** usage totals); a quota upsert logs `quota.upsert` (`action=create|replace`, who/what/when); a scope-denied PUT logs `quota.forbidden` | `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/services/events_service.py`, `src/api/routes/quotas.py` | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_rejection_is_logged_without_totals` + `test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_upsert_and_forbidden_logged` |\n34\t| AC20 (perf) | `POST /v1/events` **p95 < 50 ms** under the sustained distributed-key k6 load **with quotas active** (high limits, no rejection) — the quota-check path does not blow the existing budget | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `src/services/events_service.py`; `tests/integration/k6/load_events_quota.js` | `tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py::test_events_ingest_with_quotas_p95_under_50ms` (nearest-rank p95 over raw k6 samples) |\n35\t| AC21 (DAST-readiness) | The served `/openapi.json` includes `PUT /v1/quotas` matching the implemented route/schema; the DAST auth context documents an **admin**-scoped seeded test key (`seed_api_key.py --admin`) with the `Authorization: Bearer mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>` scheme | `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `.pipeline/plan.md`, `docs/system_architecture.md` | `tests/test_dast_context_documented.py` + `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_openapi_exposes_put_quotas` |\n36\t| AC22 | ASVS 5.0.0 L1/L2 (+ in-scope L3: V15.4.x safe concurrency, V11.2.4 constant-time) reconciliation across the change set — triggered chapters V1/V2/V4/V6/V8/V12/V13/V14/V15/V16 met or waived | security stage (`asvs` reconciliation block) | delegated: `security` (covered:false at the testing stage) |\n37\t\n38\tNotes:\n39\t- AC22 is **delegated to the security stage** (ASVS reconciliation is its deliverable, not a\n40\t  test-suite assertion) — declared in `delegated_criteria` above; testing marks it\n41\t  `covered: false, delegated: \"security\"`.\n42\t- AC20 is a measurable **performance** criterion (threshold p95 < 50 ms on `POST /v1/events`) —\n43\t  measured by testing's performance mode against the real k6 harness; it rides `criteria_covered`.\n44\t- No `data_protection` criterion is emitted: every new stored field is classified **non-sensitive\n45\t  operational config** (see plan *Data classification*), so no field-level KDF/KMS mechanism is\n46\t  required — `data_protection_waiver: all new stored fields (customer_id, metric, limit_per_window,\n47\t  scope) are non-sensitive opaque operational config already stored as identifiers; RDS SSE\n48\t  (storage-level) covers them`.\n49\t"}]},"uuid":"d9f69add-87a2-4bb0-a731-409b65f1be7a","timestamp":"2026-07-08T17:47:06.483Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"d5cb94a9-28da-4721-b049-0533922504a6","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"d9f69add-87a2-4bb0-a731-409b65f1be7a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a81b8b0ba69959f89","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq1VdY7xiWVEAwhxn4Xz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Wv9QySZJrx1dAKq9GWHq3P","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\requirements.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":25507,"cache_read_input_tokens":19208,"output_tokens":347,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":25507},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":347,"cache_read_input_tokens":19208,"cache_creation_input_tokens":25507,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":25507,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq1VcbZXaBsGoBi32H39","attributionAgent":"plan-audit","type":"assistant","uuid":"e8914c34-7747-4047-83e2-4706e7c13fe3","timestamp":"2026-07-08T17:47:06.837Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"e8914c34-7747-4047-83e2-4706e7c13fe3","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"baf21a5c-1a23-429e-9e74-122628363a90","agentId":"a81b8b0ba69959f89","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Wv9QySZJrx1dAKq9GWHq3P","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Requirements — per-customer metric quotas\n2\t\n3\tElicited 2026-07-08 (operator interview, requirements-elicitation first live run).\n4\tBrief: PROJECT.md (PUT /v1/quotas admin-scoped; POST /v1/events 429s on would-exceed;\n5\tone expand-only migration; existing p95 < 50 ms budget on POST /v1/events; no design source).\n6\t\n7\t## Resolved\n8\t\n9\t- What window is `limit_per_window`? → The existing UTC hour rollup window\n10\t  (`floor_to_hour_utc` / rollup `window_start`). The quota check reads the current-hour\n11\t  rollup; no new aggregation.\n12\t- How is a quota tenant-scoped? → Per tenant: `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)`.\n13\t  Quota rows carry the tenant key like every other table; an admin key sets quotas for\n14\t  its own tenant's customers only.\n15\t- What does \"would exceed\" mean at the boundary (rollup R, incoming quantity Q, limit L)?\n16\t  → Reject when `R + Q > L`; usage never exceeds L. An event with Q > L against an empty\n17\t  window is rejected too.\n18\t- Throttle-vs-quota precedence on POST /v1/events, and error code? → Tier-2 token-bucket\n19\t  throttle stays first (pre-handler dependency, protects the DB from quota-check load);\n20\t  quota rejections are a distinct envelope `code: quota_exceeded` (429). Existing\n21\t  throttle keeps `code: rate_limited`.\n22\t- How does a key become admin-scoped? → New `scope` column on `api_keys` (default\n23\t  `'ingest'`, expand-only), `scripts/seed_api_key.py` grows an `--admin` flag, the\n24\t  authenticated principal carries the scope, PUT /v1/quotas requires `scope = 'admin'`\n25\t  (403 `forbidden` otherwise).\n26\t- PUT /v1/quotas semantics for an existing row? → Upsert: create-or-replace\n27\t  `(customer_id, metric) → limit_per_window` (201 create / 200 replace); response body\n28\t  echoes the stored quota. No removal path this slice.\n29\t- When does a quota set/changed mid-window take effect? → Immediately, against the\n30\t  current window's already-accumulated rollup. Lowering L below current R blocks the\n31\t  rest of the window.\n32\t- Concurrent POSTs racing at the quota edge? → Strict enforcement: the quota check is\n33\t  atomic with the rollup increment inside the existing per-request transaction (guarding\n34\t  the rollup row, e.g. row lock / conditional update), so usage can never exceed L.\n35\t  Serializes concurrent posts on the same (customer, metric, window) row; the p95\n36\t  < 50 ms budget still applies.\n37\t- Idempotent replay (duplicate idempotency_key) when the window is now over quota? →\n38\t  200 replay with the original stored result; the quota is not consulted. The\n39\t  idempotency contract is absolute — a retry of an accepted event never flips to 429,\n40\t  and a replay adds no usage.\n41\t- Validation bounds on `limit_per_window`? → Integer >= 1 only; 0 and negatives are\n42\t  rejected 422 (`validation_failed`). A quota is a cap, not a kill switch.\n43\t- Extra contents of the 429 quota response? → `Retry-After` header = seconds until the\n44\t  next hour window (matches the throttle's existing header pattern). Body stays the\n45\t  standard three-field envelope `{code, message, requestId}` — no usage numbers in\n46\t  error bodies.\n47\t- The brief's \"ONE expand-only migration\" vs the new api_keys scope column? → One\n48\t  Alembic revision containing both expand-only changes: CREATE TABLE quotas + ALTER\n49\t  TABLE api_keys ADD COLUMN scope DEFAULT 'ingest' (backfill-free).\n50\t- Is PUT /v1/quotas behind the normal edge stack? → Yes: require_api_key → Tier-2\n51\t  per-key throttle → scope check (403) → handler. No admin special-casing.\n52\t- Data classification of the new stored fields (customer_id, metric, limit_per_window,\n53\t  scope)? → Non-sensitive operational config; customer_id/metric are opaque\n54\t  tenant-scoped identifiers already stored in events/rollups. Storage-level encryption\n55\t  (RDS SSE) suffices; no field-level crypto.\n56\t\n57\t## Open\n58\t\n59\t- Latency budget for PUT /v1/quotas itself — not discussed in the interview; the stated\n60\t  p95 < 50 ms budget applies to POST /v1/events only. Planning should either state a\n61\t  sensible default for the (low-traffic, admin-only) route or raise it at the plan\n62\t  checkpoint.\n63\t\n64\t## Out of scope\n65\t\n66\t- Removing/unsetting a quota (DELETE /v1/quotas or `limit: null`) — customers go back\n67\t  to unlimited only via direct DB change this slice.\n68\t- GET /v1/quotas (read/list endpoint) — the PUT response echo is the only read.\n69\t- `limit_per_window = 0` as a customer/metric kill switch — blocking a customer\n70\t  outright is a different feature.\n71\t- Global / cross-tenant quotas — quotas are per (api_key_id, customer_id, metric) only.\n72\t- Deferred effectiveness (`effective_from` / next-window-only quota changes) — changes\n73\t  apply immediately.\n74\t- Usage/limit/window-reset detail in the 429 error body.\n75\t- Daily or per-quota-configurable windows — hour windows only.\n76\t- Any change of behavior for customers without a quota row (they stay unlimited).\n77\t"}]},"uuid":"35930a9a-1b7f-456b-826f-56742eed5c26","timestamp":"2026-07-08T17:47:06.877Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e8914c34-7747-4047-83e2-4706e7c13fe3","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
