{"parentUuid":"b3ad6818-0637-4a39-b5ac-237dbadf1b88","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a81b8b0ba69959f89","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq1gdG4H6Z1HghUh6TwZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Audit complete. Summary: **2 total flags, 0 material, 0 critical, `revision_recommended: false`, 0 dependencies checked/unverified** (plan introduces no new third-party dependencies — verified against `pyproject.toml`).\n\nFindings, both advisory only:\n1. The \"no lock cycle can form\" claim (event→quota→rollup ordering) is argued structurally rather than backed by a dedicated deadlock/timeout test — reasonable but worth a one-line test note.\n2. Open Question 3 (admin-as-ingest-superset, single-key-per-tenant) is a real product constraint the plan flags honestly and deserves explicit human sign-off at the checkpoint, even though the proposed default is sound.\n\nEverything else checked clean: all layer sections present (Frontend correctly n/a for this backend-only feature), all 22 acceptance criteria traced with `acceptance.md` complete, `tasks.md` decomposition (T1–T6) fully covers AC1–AC21 with AC22 correctly delegated to security and no dangling `depends_on`, every STRIDE threat names a concrete mechanism + file, input-surface validation/rate-limit pairs present and correctly principal-keyed (not IP-keyed), data-protection classification + waiver present and correctly formatted, object-level authorization (AC6) and authentication-boundary (AC4) criteria present, safe-error handling already covered by an existing regression test at the unchanged callsite, DAST readiness and ASVS-compliance blocks present and scoped, no ambiguous prose or unresolved markers, all \"usage can never exceed L\" style proof claims name an invariant with an enforcement point and (mostly) a verifying test, and the cross-feature data-flow trace confirms the quota check reads `usage_rollup` under the same principal key that writes it (no feature-3-style reader/writer mismatch).\n\nReport written to `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\plan-audit.md`. Plan audited: `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\plan.md` (sha256 `1e74fdb8ce7250cc09861ea670fc961675aa89ba6c182b67e087d109ee02a873`), cross-referenced against `.pipeline/acceptance.md`, `.pipeline/tasks.md`, `.pipeline/requirements.md`, `PROJECT.md`, and `pyproject.toml`."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3343,"cache_read_input_tokens":62205,"output_tokens":856,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3343},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":856,"cache_read_input_tokens":62205,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3343,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3343,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq1gc9aVpA5GJkdJgqUY","attributionAgent":"plan-audit","type":"assistant","uuid":"ab4cb07f-4df4-4845-b007-29f19ec25f61","timestamp":"2026-07-08T17:49:43.285Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
